Business Brief -- Park-Ohio Industries Inc.:
   Secom General May Offer
   $30.8 Million for Company
Park-Ohio said in a statement that the proposed offer was
"subject to numerous conditions," adding that the actual
offering price could be "significantly less" than the
proposed price.
   A spokesman for Secom, a custom tooling concern, said
Park-Ohio had said it would be interested in considering
acquisition proposals from anybody. Park-Ohio considered a
sale of the company in the fall, but negotiations weren't
successful. Secom said it would finance the transaction
through NBD Corp. The company wouldn't release a copy of its
proposal.